        "comment": "The new snow and wind slabs are lying on top of a weakly bonded old snowpack. Even single winter sport participants can release avalanches in some places. In particular shady slopes are dangerous, especially in areas close to the tree line, as well as above the tree line. <br/> <br/> As a consequence of warming during the day and solar radiation loose snow avalanches are to be expected as the day progresses. This applies in particular on steep sunny slopes. <br/> <br/> In addition gliding avalanches are possible. This applies especially on cut and grassy slopes.",
